\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 20}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Do you want to be shown, you foolish person, that faith apart from works is useless? }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 21}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Was not Abraham our father justified by works when he offered up his son Isaac on the altar? }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 22}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You see that faith was active along with his works, and faith was completed by his works; }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 23}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 and the Scripture was fulfilled that says, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Abraham believed God, and it was counted to him as righteousness\u8221\'94\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 and he was called a friend of God. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 24}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 You see that a person is justified by works and not by faith alone. }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 25}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And in the same way was not also Rahab the prostitute justified by works when she received the messengers and sent them out by another way? }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b1\i0 26}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 For as the body apart from the spirit is dead, so also faith apart from works is dead.}
